The paper deals with source and channel coding over multiuser channels, which is a topic that falls under the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of correlated source side information on the optimal separation of source and channel codes, which is a topic that is relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI) sub-categories. The paper also considers the multiple access channel, the compound multiple access channel, the interference channel, and the two-way channel, which are all topics that fall under the networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the joint design criterion, which is a topic that is relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
